body:
## Problem

The `/lists/<slug>` pages (top-10 lists like fastest metal drummers, best death metal drummers, etc.) currently have `ItemList` schema in SSR (from Issue #1210) but **no `FAQPage` schema**. FAQPage would give these pages AI Overview eligibility for high-intent queries like "who is the fastest metal drummer?", "best death metal drummers of all time", etc.

Confirmed in `api/meta/[...path].js` (listMatch handler): returns `ItemList` articleSchema only — no FAQPage.

## Files to touch

- `api/meta/[...path].js` — `listMatch` handler block (search for Issue #1210)

## Template

Upgrade the existing `articleSchema` from a single `ItemList` to a `@graph` array containing both `ItemList` AND `FAQPage`:

```js
articleSchema: JSON.stringify({
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@graph': [
    {
      '@type': 'ItemList',
      name: list.title,
      description: list.seoDescription || list.description,
      url: `${BASE_URL}/lists/${listSlug}`,
      numberOfItems: list.items?.length || 10,
      publisher: { '@type': 'Organization', name: 'MetalForge', url: BASE_URL },
      // Optionally add itemListElement if list.items is available:
      itemListElement: (list.items || []).slice(0, 10).map((item, i) => ({
        '@type': 'ListItem',
        position: i + 1,
        name: item.name || item,
        url: item.url || `${BASE_URL}/drummer/${item.slug || ''}`,
      })),
    },
    {
      '@type': 'FAQPage',
      mainEntity: [
        {
          '@type': 'Question',
          name: `Who tops the ${list.title}?`,
          acceptedAnswer: {
            '@type': 'Answer',
            text: `The #1 ranked entry in ${list.title} on MetalForge is ${list.items?.[0]?.name || 'featured on the MetalForge ranked list'}. See the full ranked list at metalforge.io/lists/${listSlug}.`,
          },
        },
        {
          '@type': 'Question',
          name: `How is the ${list.title} determined?`,
          acceptedAnswer: {
            '@type': 'Answer',
            text: `The ${list.title} is curated by MetalForge editors based on technique, innovation, influence, and community recognition within the metal genre.`,
          },
        },
        {
          '@type': 'Question',
          name: `How many drummers are on the ${list.title}?`,
          acceptedAnswer: {
            '@type': 'Answer',
            text: `The ${list.title} features ${list.items?.length || 10} professional metal drummers ranked by MetalForge.`,
          },
        },
      ],
    },
  ],
}),
```

## Pages (~8 top-10 list slugs)

All slugs from `top10Lists` array in data — fastest-metal-drummers, best-death-metal-drummers, etc.

## Quality gate

- ≥3 Q&A in FAQPage
- ItemList must retain its existing data (no regression)
- Schema validates via Google Rich Results Test

## Estimated organic uplift

- AI Overview eligibility for "who is the [superlative] metal drummer?" queries
- Featured snippet eligibility for list content
- Compounds ItemList ranking signal already present

## Verify

1. Google Rich Results Test on /lists/fastest-metal-drummers → FAQPage + ItemList both valid
2. `curl -s 'https://metalforge.io/api/meta/lists/fastest-metal-drummers' | grep FAQPage` → non-empty
3. GSC: check for AI Overview appearances on "fastest metal drummer" within 3 weeks
4. No regression: ItemList still present in schema response
5. Breadcrumb still valid

## Done

When all `/lists/<slug>` handlers return `@graph` with both `ItemList` and `FAQPage` from SSR.
